{
  "name": "prog-save-continue",
  "note": "S-LIFECYCLE 1 (operator directive 2026-07-17: 'create the playwright scenario that creates a progression and saves it, then viewing the set list and clicking that progression, then clicking continue building - so you can reproduce and see what I'm seeing'). The REAL flow, no seeding: build a progression through the UI, Save through the real naming row (add-to-setlist default), open it FROM THE SETLIST, Continue building, and continue seamlessly - the section reads as a standard Verse, the dropdown is never blank, an edit updates the SAME record. Red-first vs the pre-fix label bug: the card read 'Progression' and the select went blank. S-COMPOSE-CALM (2026-07-19): jam surface carries zero song chrome; capture enters via the Save sheet, the canvas is the one song editor (Save-grow / Library-continue / draft-only Save), exits via its X.",
  "viewport": {
    "width": 412,
    "height": 915
  },
  "steps": [
    {
      "action": "goto",
      "path": "/music/play/"
    },
    {
      "action": "wait",
      "ms": 800
    },
    {
      "action": "tap",
      "selector": ".tabbar [data-tab=\"compose\"]"
    },
    {
      "action": "wait",
      "ms": 400
    },
    {
      "action": "tapChord",
      "name": "C"
    },
    {
      "action": "tapChord",
      "name": "G"
    },
    {
      "action": "tapChord",
      "name": "Am"
    },
    {
      "action": "tapChord",
      "name": "F"
    },
    {
      "action": "wait",
      "ms": 200
    },
    {
      "action": "tap",
      "selector": "#cSave"
    },
    {
      "action": "tapText",
      "text": "Save progression"
    },
    {
      "action": "waitFor",
      "selector": ".composeRow .composeRowInput"
    },
    {
      "action": "tap",
      "selector": ".composeRow .btn.red"
    },
    {
      "action": "wait",
      "ms": 500
    },
    {
      "action": "tap",
      "selector": ".tabbar [data-tab=\"jam\"]"
    },
    {
      "action": "wait",
      "ms": 400
    },
    {
      "action": "evalAssert",
      "label": "the saved progression sits at the TOP of the setlist (toTop - a just-saved progression is next up)",
      "js": "(function(){var first=document.querySelector('#setBody .listItem .li-title');return !!first && /Original progression/.test(first.textContent);})()"
    },
    {
      "action": "tap",
      "selector": "#setBody .listItem:has-text(\"Original progression\")"
    },
    {
      "action": "wait",
      "ms": 500
    },
    {
      "action": "tapText",
      "text": "Continue building"
    },
    {
      "action": "wait",
      "ms": 500
    },
    {
      "action": "evalAssert",
      "label": "Continue building lands on the Song canvas with the progression as a STANDARD Verse section (pre-fix: 'Progression')",
      "js": "(function(){var n=document.querySelector('#songSections .songSect .songSectName');return !!n && /^Verse\\b/.test(n.textContent.trim()) && /4/.test(n.textContent);})()"
    },
    {
      "action": "tap",
      "selector": "#songSections .songSect .songSectEdit"
    },
    {
      "action": "wait",
      "ms": 400
    },
    {
      "action": "evalAssert",
      "label": "the editor is SET to continue seamlessly: 4 chords loaded AND the section dropdown reads Verse - never blank (the reported bug)",
      "js": "(function(){var s=document.getElementById('songSectSel');return document.querySelectorAll('#prog .slot').length===4 && !!s && s.value==='Verse';})()"
    },
    {
      "action": "tapChord",
      "name": "Dm"
    },
    {
      "action": "wait",
      "ms": 200
    },
    {
      "action": "tap",
      "selector": "#cSave"
    },
    {
      "action": "wait",
      "ms": 350
    },
    {
      "action": "tap",
      "selector": ".composeRow.asModal .composeRowBtns button:nth-child(2)"
    },
    {
      "action": "wait",
      "ms": 500
    },
    {
      "action": "wait",
      "ms": 400
    },
    {
      "action": "tap",
      "selector": "#cSave"
    },
    {
      "action": "wait",
      "ms": 450
    },
    {
      "action": "wait",
      "ms": 400
    },
    {
      "action": "evalAssert",
      "label": "the refine UPDATED the same section in place - one card, now 5 chords, still one saved record",
      "js": "(function(){var cards=document.querySelectorAll('#songSections .songSect');var n=cards.length===1 && /5/.test(cards[0].querySelector('.songSectName').textContent);var customs=JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('roadcase-ukulele-gcea.custom.v1')||'[]');return n && customs.length===1;})()"
    },
    {
      "action": "screenshot",
      "name": "prog-save-continue"
    }
  ]
}
